<p>Alan reached. He freed his hand and reached until his elbow popped from the strain. As his fingertips grazed the light, he was washed in a brightness as the world around him melted away. This was it. The brightness faded as he rushed straight ahead it felt like. Something in his brain however faulted. He blinked hard.</p>
<p>When he opened his eyes, he was sitting on the couch. Back in the room.</p>
<p>&#171;The hell is this place?&#187; Chirped the radio on the table. Alan took a breath and he started the motions.</p>
<p>&quot;D-3454, do you copy?&quot; Alan waited for his other self's response.</p>
